Package it for pip (#25)

* Package it for pip

It is now possible to package it and distribute it as python package:
- build a package: `python3 -m build`
- install it locally (for testing) `python3 -m pip install ./dist/a2ln_server-1.1.4.tar.gz` (it generates 2 files, which both should work on)
- publish it to the testing pypi repo: `python3 -m twine upload --repository testpypi dist/*`

Resources:
- https://packaging.python.org/en/latest/tutorials/packaging-projects
- https://setuptools.pypa.io/en/latest/userguide/entry_point.html
